WEBVTT

00:01.566 --> 00:04.004
- Previously
on "Superman & Lois"...

00:04.047 --> 00:05.527
- Ally Allston merged
with her Bizarro self.

00:05.570 --> 00:06.919
Does that mean she's
some sort of god now?

00:06.963 --> 00:08.095
- That pendant gave her
a lot of power.

00:08.138 --> 00:09.618
And the Jon that came here

00:09.661 --> 00:11.315
wants to do
the same thing with you.

00:11.359 --> 00:13.143
- If Jonathan merges
with his Bizarro self,

00:13.187 --> 00:14.666
he'll be as strong as she is.
- Who's the weak one now?

00:14.710 --> 00:16.451
- Where's Dad taking him?

00:16.494 --> 00:18.366
- One of those black sites
at Holding Tower 0.

00:18.409 --> 00:20.063
- John Henry and Nat may have
sent Lana's doppelganger back,

00:20.107 --> 00:21.282
but as long as she's still
working with Ally,

00:21.325 --> 00:22.892
our Lana might not be safe.

00:22.935 --> 00:24.676
If you're all okay with it...
- Absolutely.

00:24.720 --> 00:26.243
- Lana, there's something
I've wanted to tell you

00:26.287 --> 00:28.724
my entire life.
- You're Superman.

00:30.030 --> 00:33.424
[soft music]

00:33.468 --> 00:40.823
♪

00:40.866 --> 00:43.913
You're Superman?

00:43.956 --> 00:45.436
- Kind of.

00:45.480 --> 00:48.004
- How did I not see this?

00:48.048 --> 00:51.007
How did people
not put this together?

00:51.051 --> 00:54.793
- People see
who they want to see.

00:57.840 --> 01:00.190
- How long
have you had powers?

01:00.234 --> 01:03.454
- Since we were kids.

01:03.498 --> 01:07.545
[laughter]

01:07.589 --> 01:10.418
♪

01:10.461 --> 01:12.289
- You have to do it
in a specific order.

01:12.333 --> 01:13.725
Otherwise, you...

01:13.769 --> 01:15.945
- You're the reason

01:15.988 --> 01:19.427
all that strange stuff
happened here.

01:19.470 --> 01:21.255
All of it was you...

01:21.298 --> 01:28.262
♪

01:28.305 --> 01:31.395
Including the accident.

01:31.439 --> 01:32.701
I love you, Clark.

01:32.744 --> 01:35.182
- Pete!

01:40.839 --> 01:43.059
- You saved us.

01:45.366 --> 01:47.194
- Couldn't let my friends
get hurt.

01:47.237 --> 01:50.893
- But I did get hurt.

01:50.936 --> 01:54.940
You vanished
almost right after that night.

01:54.984 --> 01:57.247
- Look, I had to figure out
who I was.

01:57.291 --> 01:58.727
My dad was gone.

01:58.770 --> 02:00.337
My mom didn't want me
using my powers.

02:00.381 --> 02:04.950
I-I was angry
and confused.

02:04.994 --> 02:07.692
But after saving you
and Pete that night,

02:07.736 --> 02:11.392
I finally understood what
I was meant to do with my life.

02:11.435 --> 02:15.787
And as soon as
I realized that,

02:15.831 --> 02:19.269
I knew I couldn't stay
in Smallville anymore...

02:19.313 --> 02:21.228
no matter
how much I wanted to.

02:21.271 --> 02:24.187
- That's why you left...

02:24.231 --> 02:26.755
to become Superman.

02:28.235 --> 02:30.324
[scoffs]

02:32.064 --> 02:34.241
Why didn't you come
back for me?

02:34.284 --> 02:36.025
- I did.

02:36.068 --> 02:37.766
You were with Kyle.

02:39.898 --> 02:41.813
- Hi.
Mmm.

02:45.252 --> 02:47.254
You should have told me.

02:47.297 --> 02:51.606
♪

02:51.649 --> 02:54.652
Did you ever love me?

02:57.046 --> 02:59.004
- Lana, of course I did.

03:00.267 --> 03:02.486
- Just not enough.

03:05.097 --> 03:07.404
- Lana, I'm sorry.

03:10.233 --> 03:11.930
- I got to go.

03:17.458 --> 03:20.417
[dramatic music]

03:20.461 --> 03:27.424
♪

03:27.468 --> 03:30.253
- You guys are not
telling us the full story.

03:30.297 --> 03:32.124
All right, there's
no way that you told

03:32.168 --> 03:33.691
Mrs. Cushing
that you're Superman,

03:33.735 --> 03:35.302
and then she just drove away--
that's insane.

03:35.345 --> 03:36.694
- That's what she did.

03:36.738 --> 03:38.261
- We knew she would be hurt.

03:38.305 --> 03:39.697
- Didn't know
she'd be that hurt.

03:39.741 --> 03:40.872
- I kind of knew.

03:40.916 --> 03:42.396
- What was she like at the end?

03:42.439 --> 03:43.745
Like, do you think
she's gonna tell Sarah?

03:43.788 --> 03:44.963
Did you even ask?

03:45.007 --> 03:46.443
- Jordan,
leave your father alone.

03:46.487 --> 03:48.358
Jonathan, where
is your backpack?

03:48.402 --> 03:50.273
You're gonna be late
for school.

03:50.317 --> 03:51.883
- I still can't even believe
you're making us go to school.

03:51.927 --> 03:53.668
- Of course
you have to go to school.

03:53.711 --> 03:56.061
We are lucky Principal Balcomb
even accepted you back.

03:56.105 --> 03:59.239
And side note--as long as the
other you is still locked up,

03:59.282 --> 04:01.153
you are technically safer
than anyone else.

04:01.197 --> 04:02.981
- What does that even mean--
I'm technically safer

04:03.025 --> 04:04.635
than anyone else?

04:04.679 --> 04:06.115
- Your doppelganger
was Ally's first horseman,

04:06.158 --> 04:07.725
but I doubt
he'll be her last.

04:07.769 --> 04:09.249
- Well, then maybe
we should stay home,

04:09.292 --> 04:11.076
you know, in case you guys
need our help.

04:11.120 --> 04:12.687
- Well, if we need your help,
then we'll know

04:12.730 --> 04:14.166
exactly where to find you,
won't we?

04:14.210 --> 04:17.344
Let's go.
- Go.

04:17.387 --> 04:19.302
You really think Ally's gonna
send more of her acolytes?

04:19.346 --> 04:20.608
- She already has.

04:20.651 --> 04:21.957
I mean, John Henry and Nat

04:22.000 --> 04:23.915
may have sent Lana-Rho
back to her world,

04:23.959 --> 04:25.526
but it doesn't mean
she won't try again

04:25.569 --> 04:27.179
or that Ally
won't show up herself.

04:27.223 --> 04:29.312
- Well, that's why we have
to warn our Lana, Clark.

04:29.356 --> 04:30.487
- She won't return my calls.

04:30.531 --> 04:32.184
- Let me just reach out,

04:32.228 --> 04:33.838
and I'm gonna try to smooth
things over for you two.

04:33.882 --> 04:35.753
- In the meantime,
while your dad and John Henry

04:35.797 --> 04:37.712
are running tests
on the pendant, I will see

04:37.755 --> 04:39.757
if I can try to figure out
what Ally's next move is.

04:39.801 --> 04:43.239
- After you drop the boys off.
- Of course.

04:43.283 --> 04:44.458
- Clark.

04:46.634 --> 04:48.331
It's gonna take Lana
a little while

04:48.375 --> 04:51.552
to wrap her head around this.

04:51.595 --> 04:53.467
- Yeah.

04:55.556 --> 04:58.602
[school bell rings]

05:00.604 --> 05:02.693
- S-she's coming.

05:02.737 --> 05:08.612
♪

05:08.656 --> 05:10.005
- She's not gonna stop.

05:10.048 --> 05:11.572
- S-she will
if you say hi to her.

05:11.615 --> 05:15.532
- I'm not gonna--Hey, Sarah.
- Hey, Natalie.

05:15.576 --> 05:18.013
- Told you.

05:18.056 --> 05:21.756
- Look what the cat dragged in.
- What's up, guys?

05:21.799 --> 05:23.584
- So, uh, Kent,

05:23.627 --> 05:25.368
have you figured out a way
to get the baseball season

05:25.412 --> 05:27.196
canceled yet?
- [snickers]

05:27.239 --> 05:28.719
- I mean,
since you ruined football.

05:28.763 --> 05:30.155
- Okay, whatever.

05:30.199 --> 05:31.418
At least I didn't snitch
on you guys.

05:31.461 --> 05:32.984
You should be thanking me.

05:33.028 --> 05:34.769
Besides, this guy
was literally huffing

05:34.812 --> 05:36.684
more of that stuff
than I was.

05:36.727 --> 05:38.468
- Maybe, but I didn't get
the whole season canceled.

05:38.512 --> 05:40.383
- So what? What, you think any
of this matters?

05:40.427 --> 05:41.428
You think football matters?

05:41.471 --> 05:42.951
You think baseball matters?

05:42.994 --> 05:44.387
You think even
high school matters?

05:44.431 --> 05:45.693
All of it's meaningless.
- Uh, Jon, uh--

05:45.736 --> 05:47.564
- Okay, you have no idea

05:47.608 --> 05:49.566
that it's about to be the end
of the world as we know it.

05:49.610 --> 05:52.656
- Uh, he just started following
Greta Thunberg on Twitter.

05:52.700 --> 05:56.181
- Climate change.
Scary stuff.

05:58.140 --> 06:00.185
- You're a freak, Kent.

06:04.625 --> 06:06.496
- What the hell was that?

06:06.540 --> 06:08.193
- It's nothing.
It's fine.

06:08.237 --> 06:10.239
- No, you are definitely not
fine, which is totally cool,

06:10.282 --> 06:12.241
considering what you've been
through, but...

06:12.284 --> 06:15.766
maybe you shouldn't be here.

06:15.810 --> 06:17.899
- Where do you want to go?

06:20.118 --> 06:22.338
- Follow me.

06:22.382 --> 06:25.646
- You're gonna skip
on your first day back?

06:25.689 --> 06:29.084
[school bell rings]

06:29.127 --> 06:31.173
We're so gonna get busted.

06:33.567 --> 06:36.918
- You look exactly the same
as you did in high school.

06:36.961 --> 06:38.310
- Good genes, I guess.

06:38.354 --> 06:40.182
- You have the same look
on your face,

06:40.225 --> 06:42.445
like you got the weight
of the world on your shoulders.

06:42.489 --> 06:44.012
- You know,
you don't have to do this.

06:44.055 --> 06:45.448
There's always another way.

06:45.492 --> 06:47.276
- I don't think
you really believe that.

06:47.319 --> 06:50.627
- You're the hero
right now, Lana.

06:50.671 --> 06:52.499
- Also, did Superman
just lie to me?

06:52.542 --> 06:53.804
- [chuckles]

06:53.848 --> 06:55.719
- Lana. Lana.

06:55.763 --> 06:58.592
Earth to Lana.
Hey.

06:58.635 --> 07:01.508
- Hey, Kyle.Sorry.

07:01.551 --> 07:04.685
- [sighs] You were really
zoning out there.

07:04.728 --> 07:07.818
- Well, I just didn't get
a lot of sleep last night.

07:07.862 --> 07:09.907
- Yeah, you didn't
call me back either.

07:11.561 --> 07:14.956
Uh, just--I wanted to see
how things went with Sarah.

07:16.523 --> 07:18.655
The car?

07:18.699 --> 07:21.484
Did she love the car?
- Oh, yeah.

07:21.528 --> 07:23.617
Yeah, she did.
I'm sorry.

07:23.660 --> 07:26.141
I-I should have called
you back.

07:26.184 --> 07:28.273
- It's fine.
Um...

07:28.317 --> 07:29.927
so did y'all take it
for a spin?

07:29.971 --> 07:33.496
- Actually,
we didn't get a chance.

07:33.540 --> 07:35.585
- Why not?

07:35.629 --> 07:39.850
[cell phone buzzes]

07:39.894 --> 07:43.201
- Oh, God, I really can't talk.

07:43.245 --> 07:46.596
Can you do me a favor and, um,
pick up the girls from school?

07:46.640 --> 07:48.598
- Yeah. Sure.

07:48.642 --> 07:50.382
- Thank you.

07:50.426 --> 07:52.341
- Important call?

07:52.384 --> 07:54.822
- Oh, just my new assistant
wondering where I am.

07:54.865 --> 07:57.128
Got to go.

07:57.172 --> 07:58.565
- Bye.

08:00.741 --> 08:02.264
[door opens, bells jingle]

08:04.396 --> 08:06.703
[whooshing]

08:06.747 --> 08:08.400
- What are you doing here?

08:08.444 --> 08:10.707
- I was hoping we could talk.

08:10.751 --> 08:12.361
- I have nothing to say to you.

08:12.404 --> 08:14.102
- You're angry.

08:14.145 --> 08:15.712
From what I could tell,

08:15.756 --> 08:18.541
you didn't exactly have
the best...

08:18.585 --> 08:21.762
support system over there.

08:21.805 --> 08:23.764
- My family? Supportive?

08:23.807 --> 08:26.331
- And I'm sorry for that.
You deserve better.

08:26.375 --> 08:29.378
But you made a lot
of bad choices,

08:29.421 --> 08:31.293
ones that cost
people their lives.

08:31.336 --> 08:34.862
And that's on you.
- [sighs]

08:34.905 --> 08:41.869
♪

08:41.912 --> 08:43.697
[sighs]

08:43.740 --> 08:46.264
You really come all the way
here just to tell me that?

08:46.308 --> 08:47.439
- I came here because
I think there's more

08:47.483 --> 08:49.093
to you than what I've seen.

08:49.137 --> 08:51.269
You're a good kid
who went down the wrong path,

08:51.313 --> 08:53.184
and I want to give you
the chance to make up

08:53.228 --> 08:55.056
for some of the hurt
you've caused.

08:55.099 --> 08:56.405
- Yeah?
How's that?

08:56.448 --> 08:58.581
- Help me save your world...

08:58.625 --> 09:00.975
and mine.

09:01.018 --> 09:03.064
Help me stop Ally.

09:06.502 --> 09:10.201
- You know, maybe...

09:10.245 --> 09:13.683
maybe if my dad had ever...

09:13.727 --> 09:15.685
I don't know,
just talked to me

09:15.729 --> 09:19.210
the way you are right now,
maybe I'd be on your side.

09:22.039 --> 09:23.345
But he didn't.

09:23.388 --> 09:25.477
- Tell me what she's planning.

09:25.521 --> 09:28.219
- You know the answer to that.

09:28.263 --> 09:30.874
She's gonna fix the worlds.
- No, she isn't.

09:32.528 --> 09:34.617
Because I have the pendant.

09:34.661 --> 09:37.794
And after I destroy it--
- You can't destroy it.

09:37.838 --> 09:41.450
[scoffs] My father
already tried and failed.

09:41.493 --> 09:43.278
And you'll fail, too.

09:43.321 --> 09:45.410
When she realizes
that I'm not coming back,

09:45.454 --> 09:47.021
she's gonna come here,

09:47.064 --> 09:50.894
and she's gonna take
what's rightfully hers.

09:50.938 --> 09:54.637
You saw her, Superman.

09:54.681 --> 09:57.248
Ally's a God.

09:57.292 --> 09:59.599
The people on my Earth
are gonna merge

09:59.642 --> 10:01.296
with the people
on your Earth,

10:01.339 --> 10:04.865
and there's absolutely nothing
you can do to stop it.

10:04.908 --> 10:07.955
♪

10:12.960 --> 10:15.092
- I wish I had better news,
but that kid's right.

10:15.136 --> 10:18.139
The pendant's nearly
impossible to destroy.

10:18.182 --> 10:19.662
- You're saying
it's indestructible.

10:19.706 --> 10:21.403
- Not indestructible, per se.

10:21.446 --> 10:23.927
- But the amount
of concentrated energy

10:23.971 --> 10:25.581
it would take to destroy it
is a lot more

10:25.625 --> 10:27.322
than what you can supply,

10:27.365 --> 10:30.760
and using any tech we have
here, much too dangerous.

10:30.804 --> 10:34.068
- Well, dangerous is one thing.
Impossible is something else.

10:34.111 --> 10:35.983
I'm gonna need a little time
to think about it.

10:36.026 --> 10:38.159
- We may have a better idea.

10:40.727 --> 10:42.293
- What is it?

10:42.337 --> 10:43.991
- Show him the plans.

10:44.034 --> 10:46.994
[dramatic music]

10:47.037 --> 10:53.391
♪

10:53.435 --> 10:54.654
- You want to destroy
the portal.

10:54.697 --> 10:56.046
- A controlled explosion.

10:56.090 --> 10:57.831
- That would make
the mines inoperable.

10:57.874 --> 11:00.224
- Small price to pay
for saving the world.

11:00.268 --> 11:02.879
- Yeah, our world maybe,
but what about theirs?

11:02.923 --> 11:04.664
Yes, destroying the portal

11:04.707 --> 11:06.143
prevents Ally's followers
from coming here,

11:06.187 --> 11:07.710
but it also keeps us
from getting back there.

11:07.754 --> 11:09.364
- You're worried
about our new prisoner?

11:09.407 --> 11:10.800
- And what
about all the innocent people

11:10.844 --> 11:12.541
whose lives are being destroyedby Ally?

11:12.584 --> 11:14.325
They have no one left
over there to protect them.

11:14.369 --> 11:15.544
They're gonna need our help.

11:15.587 --> 11:17.459
- You can't save
everybody, Clark.

11:17.502 --> 11:18.852
- I have to try.

11:18.895 --> 11:20.505
It's the promise I made,
the promise we made.

11:20.549 --> 11:22.072
- You don't know
what's happened

11:22.116 --> 11:23.508
on her world since you left.

11:23.552 --> 11:25.075
You need to concentrate
on this one.

11:25.119 --> 11:26.686
- He's right.

11:26.729 --> 11:28.644
We do what we can
with the information we have.

11:28.688 --> 11:30.777
We save our own.

11:30.820 --> 11:32.779
- [scoffs]
Correct me if I'm wrong.

11:32.822 --> 11:34.911
The last time the two
of you came up with a plan

11:34.955 --> 11:38.567
to do that,
it was by killing me.

11:38.610 --> 11:41.222
- In the moment, it seemed
like our only option.

11:41.265 --> 11:42.397
- Exactly my point.

11:42.440 --> 11:44.573
There's always another way.

11:44.616 --> 11:46.880
And we're gonna find one.

11:49.578 --> 11:52.146
[knock at door]

11:52.189 --> 11:54.757
- I lied to Kyle...

11:54.801 --> 11:58.500
which, for the record,
is something I have never done.

11:58.543 --> 12:00.415
- Yeah, of course.

12:00.458 --> 12:01.764
- Don't say "of course"

12:01.808 --> 12:03.157
like you know
what I'm talking about.

12:03.200 --> 12:04.506
- I'm sorry.

12:04.549 --> 12:06.160
I understand
why you're mad at Clark.

12:06.203 --> 12:08.423
- I'm not mad at Clark.

12:08.466 --> 12:09.641
- You're not?

12:09.685 --> 12:11.252
- I was mad at him.

12:11.295 --> 12:12.819
Then I tried
to put myself in his shoes

12:12.862 --> 12:14.864
and realized I couldn't.

12:14.908 --> 12:16.387
The man literally carries

12:16.431 --> 12:18.999
the weight of the world
on his shoulders.

12:19.042 --> 12:23.786
When he figured out who he was,
what he was, he was just a kid.

12:23.830 --> 12:25.570
We were kids.

12:25.614 --> 12:28.878
I don't blame him for not
telling me the truth back then.

12:28.922 --> 12:31.794
It hurts,
but I can't be mad about it.

12:31.838 --> 12:33.622
- Are you sure?
'Cause you seem kind of mad.

12:33.665 --> 12:36.233
- I'm mad at you.
- Me?

12:36.277 --> 12:37.452
- When you moved to Smallville,

12:37.495 --> 12:39.193
we didn't have
to become friends.

12:39.236 --> 12:42.022
We could have been neighborly,
waving hello at the bus stop,

12:42.065 --> 12:44.851
but you sought me out,
and I trusted you.

12:44.894 --> 12:47.375
- Lana, I understand how
this must feel for you.

12:47.418 --> 12:50.334
- No, you don't, Lois,

12:50.378 --> 12:52.728
because I've told you a lot.

12:52.772 --> 12:54.991
After Sarah's quinceañera,

12:55.035 --> 12:59.648
when my marriage was
falling apart, I called you.

12:59.691 --> 13:03.434
You've become
the person that I call.

13:03.478 --> 13:06.698
And this whole time
you've been keeping

13:06.742 --> 13:08.439
this huge secret from me.

13:08.483 --> 13:10.093
- It wasn't my secret
to share.

13:10.137 --> 13:11.921
- But you knew,
and I didn't,

13:11.965 --> 13:16.230
which means our entire
friendship was built on a lie.

13:16.273 --> 13:17.840
There's nothing real
between us.

13:17.884 --> 13:19.233
- Please don't say that.

13:19.276 --> 13:22.453
It's not true,
and it's not how I feel.

13:22.497 --> 13:25.021
- Maybe not...

13:25.065 --> 13:28.590
but it is how I feel.

13:28.633 --> 13:30.897
And the worst part about it

13:30.940 --> 13:33.247
is that you've made me
a liar, too.

13:33.290 --> 13:38.861
♪

13:38.905 --> 13:42.865
- Okay, remember, guys,
you can't tell anyone.

13:45.172 --> 13:46.956
Not even your parents.

13:47.000 --> 13:48.697
- Obviously.

13:48.740 --> 13:50.394
- Uh, maybe
you shouldn't show us.

13:50.438 --> 13:52.179
- Look, I'm not trying
to get you guys in trouble,

13:52.222 --> 13:53.963
but don't you feel like
our parents still view us all

13:54.007 --> 13:55.356
as little kids?

13:55.399 --> 13:57.184
- All the time.
- Yeah, sometimes.

13:57.227 --> 14:00.535
- So I decided to do
something about it.

14:02.406 --> 14:05.496
- Whoa.

14:05.540 --> 14:07.759
- You built
your own kill suit?

14:10.110 --> 14:11.720
- It's still very much
a work in progress,

14:11.763 --> 14:13.113
but the bones are there.

14:13.156 --> 14:15.071
- How did you figure out
how to do this?

14:15.115 --> 14:16.725
- Basically designed
my dad's suit.

14:16.768 --> 14:18.858
- So is this for you?
- It was.

14:18.901 --> 14:20.903
But after your run-in
with your lookalike,

14:20.947 --> 14:22.905
I thought you might need it
more than I do.

14:22.949 --> 14:25.299
It should prevent
any more nonconsensual merging.

14:25.342 --> 14:26.996
- [laughs]
This is--I mean,

14:27.040 --> 14:28.911
this is the coolest present
I've ever gotten.

14:28.955 --> 14:31.392
- Yeah, and we have the PS5.
- Okay, don't get too excited.

14:31.435 --> 14:33.089
It doesn't actually work yet.

14:33.133 --> 14:35.875
In order to power the suit
I still need the key component,

14:35.918 --> 14:37.224
but I can't get it by myself.

14:37.267 --> 14:39.530
I need your help
digging it out.

14:41.097 --> 14:42.664
- Okay. Where to?

14:42.707 --> 14:45.754
[doors clanging]

14:48.496 --> 14:50.411
- Were you aware
that the discovery of gold

14:50.454 --> 14:52.543
at Sutter's Mill in 1848

14:52.587 --> 14:54.328
sparked the largest migration

14:54.371 --> 14:56.591
in the history
of the United States?

14:56.634 --> 14:59.420
- I wouldn't have taken you for
much of a human history buff.

14:59.463 --> 15:02.423
- There's only so many times
a grown man can read

15:02.466 --> 15:04.816
"The Fault in Our Stars."

15:04.860 --> 15:06.775
It's been a while, brother.

15:06.818 --> 15:09.473
I was beginning to think
you'd forgotten all about me.

15:09.517 --> 15:12.346
- Actually, you and I just
spent a bit of time together.

15:12.389 --> 15:15.784
- You crossed over.

15:15.827 --> 15:17.655
Well, what was it like?

15:17.699 --> 15:19.222
Did you meet my wife?

15:19.266 --> 15:20.876
- Would you believe me
if I told you

15:20.920 --> 15:22.573
that you helped save
my son's life?

15:22.617 --> 15:24.010
- Of course I would.

15:24.053 --> 15:25.446
In any other world, brother,

15:25.489 --> 15:26.882
you and I are
the best of friends.

15:26.926 --> 15:29.363
It's only in this one
that you find yourself

15:29.406 --> 15:31.147
unable to trust me.

15:31.191 --> 15:33.802
- Maybe I could...

15:33.845 --> 15:35.935
if you helped me here and now.

15:35.978 --> 15:38.589
- There's always an "if"
with you, isn't there?

15:38.633 --> 15:40.940
- I need to destroy
Ally's pendant.

15:40.983 --> 15:42.898
I can't do it alone, but
if we combined our strength--

15:42.942 --> 15:45.857
- Cut to the chase.
What would I get in return?

15:45.901 --> 15:48.817
- Well, for starters, I could
bring you some new books.

15:48.860 --> 15:51.907
- Oh, a library card.
How very generous of you.

15:51.951 --> 15:53.953
- If you're asking
to be released--

15:53.996 --> 15:56.085
- I wouldn't waste a wish on
something I know I can't have.

15:56.129 --> 15:58.392
- Then what do you want?

15:58.435 --> 15:59.567
- Simple.

15:59.610 --> 16:03.005
I want my brother back.

16:04.833 --> 16:07.009
- Like I said,
this would be a first step

16:07.053 --> 16:09.011
to building
that kind of relationship.

16:09.055 --> 16:12.580
- Please. I saved your life,
and it still wasn't enough.

16:12.623 --> 16:15.626
Nothing I do
will ever be enough...

16:15.670 --> 16:20.153
because it's not you
I have to convince, is it?

16:20.196 --> 16:25.854
♪

16:25.897 --> 16:27.943
[door closes]
- Clark?

16:27.987 --> 16:29.292
Clark?

16:29.336 --> 16:32.817
Guess who Lana
hates more than you.

16:32.861 --> 16:34.123
- Uh, Kyle?

16:34.167 --> 16:36.386
- No, me!
Can you believe it?

16:36.430 --> 16:38.040
Of course you can't,
because it makes no sense,

16:38.084 --> 16:40.042
and it's just another
classic example

16:40.086 --> 16:42.088
of women holding each other
to higher standards

16:42.131 --> 16:43.089
than we hold men.

16:43.132 --> 16:44.742
- No, I know, I know, babe.

16:44.786 --> 16:46.744
And I want to hear
all about it, but right now

16:46.788 --> 16:48.703
there's someone here
who wants to talk to you.

16:50.879 --> 16:53.316
Just follow me.

16:56.711 --> 17:01.672
♪

17:01.716 --> 17:03.761
- Hello, Lois.

17:10.203 --> 17:12.248
- What the hell
is he doing here?

17:12.292 --> 17:15.295
- [sighs] It's complicated, but
if I'm gonna have any chance

17:15.338 --> 17:17.253
of destroying Ally's pendant,
I need his help.

17:17.297 --> 17:19.255
- I've come to try
and make amends.

17:19.299 --> 17:20.909
- Oh, really?

17:20.952 --> 17:23.085
Well, which part did you
want me to forgive first--

17:23.129 --> 17:24.956
how you kidnapped my son?

17:25.000 --> 17:26.871
Or how you tried to eradicate
all of humanity?

17:26.915 --> 17:28.264
- Lois.
- Or was it when you rewrote

17:28.308 --> 17:29.700
my article in
the "Daily Planet"?

17:29.744 --> 17:31.398
- I told you
she'd bring that up.

17:31.441 --> 17:33.095
- Okay, Lois, please, will you
just hear him out, for me?

17:33.139 --> 17:35.271
- Why should I?
- Because just listen to him.

17:35.315 --> 17:39.101
- Lois, I'm not expecting you
to forgive me.

17:39.145 --> 17:41.103
I hope only
that you'll allow me to explain

17:41.147 --> 17:43.366
what I've only
recently discovered myself.

17:43.410 --> 17:46.152
My father sent me on a path
when I was a child,

17:46.195 --> 17:48.023
a-a very painful one.

17:48.067 --> 17:50.460
But I was convinced
that if I fulfilled his dreams,

17:50.504 --> 17:53.115
then my own
might also come true,

17:53.159 --> 17:57.293
that I may one day be reunited
with my brother.

17:57.337 --> 18:00.905
I had no idea that Kal already
had a family of his own,

18:00.949 --> 18:05.736
and when he chose you
over me, I got angry.

18:05.780 --> 18:08.304
- Wow.
Is everything my fault today?

18:08.348 --> 18:11.612
- I saw you as an obstacle
that I needed to overcome.

18:11.655 --> 18:14.136
But I was wrong.

18:14.180 --> 18:16.965
I see that now,
and I'm sorry.

18:17.008 --> 18:19.533
If I hadn't wasted so much time
doing someone else's bidding,

18:19.576 --> 18:22.666
I might have found
a family here in all of you.

18:22.710 --> 18:24.233
We'll never know.

18:24.277 --> 18:26.670
But you can trust me, Lois,
when I tell you

18:26.714 --> 18:29.978
I will never hurt anyone
you love again.

18:30.021 --> 18:32.981
[dramatic music]

18:33.024 --> 18:34.591
♪

18:34.635 --> 18:37.159
Someone's coming.
- It's John Henry and your dad.

18:37.203 --> 18:38.552
We've got to get you
out of here.

18:38.595 --> 18:40.467
- You're not going anywhere.

18:42.251 --> 18:44.079
- If I thought for one second

18:44.123 --> 18:46.734
that you would take
the information we gave you

18:46.777 --> 18:48.301
and bring it to this guy--

18:48.344 --> 18:50.520
- I had no choice.
- We gave you a choice.

18:50.564 --> 18:53.044
- Dooming an entire
civilization to a merciless god

18:53.088 --> 18:54.263
is hardly a choice.

18:54.307 --> 18:55.917
You of all people
should know that.

18:55.960 --> 18:57.397
- I'm sorry, Clark,
I know he's your brother,

18:57.440 --> 18:58.963
but that doesn't mean
we can trust him.

18:59.007 --> 19:00.835
- I'm not asking you
to trust him.

19:00.878 --> 19:02.489
I'm asking you to trust me.
- Clark, he is a sociopath.

19:02.532 --> 19:04.317
- There's no need
for name-calling.

19:04.360 --> 19:06.362
- Enough!

19:06.406 --> 19:08.886
Look, I don't love the plan
either, but Clark is right.

19:08.930 --> 19:10.192
It's the best one we have,

19:10.236 --> 19:12.368
and every second
we waste arguing,

19:12.412 --> 19:14.240
we leave ourselves
and the people we love

19:14.283 --> 19:17.591
vulnerable to Ally's next move,
like Lana and Lucy.

19:17.634 --> 19:20.028
Ally is gonna get to Lucy
before we do,

19:20.071 --> 19:22.465
and you know it, Dad.

19:22.509 --> 19:24.206
So just figure this out.

19:24.250 --> 19:26.556
I have something
I have to do.

19:26.600 --> 19:30.386
♪

19:30.430 --> 19:31.387
- [sighs]

19:31.431 --> 19:33.389
- What's your idea?

19:35.348 --> 19:37.654
- The DOD got rid
of most of the X-K.

19:37.698 --> 19:40.091
My dad and I found some near
the portal the other day,

19:40.135 --> 19:42.181
so I don't think
they got all of it.

19:42.224 --> 19:45.096
- So that's where we're going?
- No.

19:45.140 --> 19:47.011
There's too many soldiers
guarding it.

19:47.055 --> 19:49.579
The map said there were
other caverns further in.

19:49.623 --> 19:50.972
- Nat, why don't we just
use some from the stash

19:51.015 --> 19:52.713
you got with your dad?

19:52.756 --> 19:55.106
- 'Cause if he saw any missing,
he'd know something was up.

19:55.150 --> 19:56.630
I don't need another lecture

19:56.673 --> 19:58.980
on not interfering
in adult situations.

19:59.023 --> 20:02.201
- I get those a lot.
- [scoffs] Yeah.

20:02.244 --> 20:04.855
I still can't believe you're
using X-K to power the suit.

20:04.899 --> 20:06.379
- Well, in their purest form,

20:06.422 --> 20:10.121
those crystals contain
an insane amount of energy.

20:10.165 --> 20:13.081
And I think we just hit...

20:13.124 --> 20:14.648
the mother lode.

20:14.691 --> 20:21.437
♪

20:21.481 --> 20:23.918
Let's get to work.

20:23.961 --> 20:26.921
[music playing softly
through headphones]

20:26.964 --> 20:30.664
♪

20:30.707 --> 20:32.318
- Sarah.

20:32.361 --> 20:34.189
Come on.
You got me today.

20:36.496 --> 20:38.237
- Where's Mom?

20:38.280 --> 20:39.760
- No idea.

20:39.803 --> 20:42.545
That woman is full
of secrets lately.

20:42.589 --> 20:44.721
- Yep.

20:44.765 --> 20:47.289
- Hey, um...

20:47.333 --> 20:50.684
is there something going on
that I should know about?

20:50.727 --> 20:55.210
This morning your mom was
just, uh...just off.

20:55.254 --> 20:56.907
- I don't know.
Maybe.

20:56.951 --> 20:59.693
I mean, she did got for, like,
a six-hour walk yesterday,

20:59.736 --> 21:01.303
so...

21:01.347 --> 21:03.174
- Who the hell goes
for a six-hour walk?

21:03.218 --> 21:04.915
- Oh, Dad,
I wouldn't be too worried.

21:04.959 --> 21:08.310
I mean, a worry is a wish
for something you don't want.

21:08.354 --> 21:11.313
Learned that
in therapy, so...

21:11.357 --> 21:13.707
- Well, that's money
well spent.

21:13.750 --> 21:15.883
[chuckles]

21:15.926 --> 21:17.406
Come on,
we got to go get your sister,

21:17.450 --> 21:21.192
get her to ballet, all right?
- Mm-hmm.

21:21.236 --> 21:23.151
- It's getting pretty late--
if we don't get home soon,

21:23.194 --> 21:25.109
Mom and Dad
are gonna start texting us.

21:25.153 --> 21:26.937
- Yeah.
How much more do we need?

21:26.981 --> 21:29.897
- [sighs]
More than this.

21:29.940 --> 21:32.116
God, I wish we had
my dad's rock-grinder thingy.

21:32.160 --> 21:34.205
- Let me guess--
another awesome invention?

21:34.249 --> 21:36.860
Jeez, you guys sure do make
being smart cool.

21:36.904 --> 21:38.862
- I have an idea.

21:38.906 --> 21:42.518
Step back.
- All right.

21:42.562 --> 21:44.868
[tool clangs]

21:44.912 --> 21:47.871
[dramatic music]

21:47.915 --> 21:53.921
♪

21:53.964 --> 21:55.966
Screw smart.
I'd rather have powers.

21:56.010 --> 21:58.534
- [chuckles]

21:58.578 --> 22:05.541
♪

22:05.585 --> 22:08.588
[rumbling]

22:08.631 --> 22:11.199
- Um, guys?

22:11.242 --> 22:12.809
- It's gonna cave in.

22:17.858 --> 22:19.512
- Run!

22:19.555 --> 22:22.471
[dramatic music]

22:22.515 --> 22:29.565
♪

22:32.089 --> 22:34.918
[all coughing]
- [sighs]

22:34.962 --> 22:36.485
- [laughs]

22:36.529 --> 22:38.095
- A-are you guys okay?
- Yeah.

22:38.139 --> 22:40.271
- Yeah.
I mean, not to bum you out,

22:40.315 --> 22:41.708
but if Sarah
ever sees you do that,

22:41.751 --> 22:43.274
you guys are definitely
getting back together.

22:43.318 --> 22:44.667
- Yeah, dude.
- You think so?

22:44.711 --> 22:46.103
- Yeah. Yeah.

22:46.147 --> 22:47.583
- Wait, guys.

22:47.627 --> 22:49.237
Where's the bag of X-K?

22:50.586 --> 22:52.109
- You sure this is gonna work?

22:52.153 --> 22:55.025
- It's like Jon-El said,
I can't do it alone.

22:55.069 --> 22:56.940
But my mother thought
the other Kal-El and I

22:56.984 --> 22:58.812
would have a chance
if we tried together.

22:58.855 --> 23:00.988
- This was Mother's idea?
- Mm.

23:01.031 --> 23:02.946
- And the thought
of using maybe your brother

23:02.990 --> 23:05.166
instead of that thing
never crossed her mind?

23:05.209 --> 23:06.254
- Tal.

23:06.297 --> 23:07.516
- Some things never change.

23:07.560 --> 23:08.909
- What do your readings say?

23:08.952 --> 23:10.345
- That his mom was right.

23:10.389 --> 23:14.523
♪

23:14.567 --> 23:16.525
These two should be
more than enough.

23:16.569 --> 23:19.354
- Well, then...
no time like the present.

23:19.398 --> 23:23.445
♪

23:23.489 --> 23:25.491
- Ready?

23:25.534 --> 23:27.275
- Just one thing...

23:27.318 --> 23:30.452
♪

23:30.496 --> 23:32.323
- ♪ Dust it all off

23:32.367 --> 23:35.414
♪ Put my head down

23:35.457 --> 23:38.373
♪ And just breathe

23:38.417 --> 23:40.244
- Hey.
- Hey.

23:40.288 --> 23:42.986
♪ And just breathe

23:43.030 --> 23:44.379
- What's that?

23:44.423 --> 23:47.164
One of those new
Olivia Rodrigo songs?

23:47.208 --> 23:49.689
- Actually, it's one of my own.

23:49.732 --> 23:52.387
- Oh, you're writing
your own songs now.

23:52.431 --> 23:54.084
- Yeah, I'm trying to work
through the rage.

23:54.128 --> 23:55.434
It--it helps.

23:55.477 --> 23:57.131
- I can see that.

23:58.698 --> 24:01.570
Well, hell, you got enough
here for an entire album.

24:01.614 --> 24:03.964
- I mean, that's
kind of the goal, right?

24:04.007 --> 24:06.357
So...give it.

24:06.401 --> 24:08.447
Thank you.

24:08.490 --> 24:12.886
- Um...so, hey, you know,
I was--I was thinking a bit

24:12.929 --> 24:16.498
more about--about your mama...
- Mm-hmm.

24:16.542 --> 24:20.981
- And, uh, this walk
that she went on.

24:21.024 --> 24:23.897
You think that she was
with someone?

24:23.940 --> 24:25.376
- Huh?

24:25.420 --> 24:29.816
- Well, like--like--
like a--like, a guy?

24:29.859 --> 24:33.472
- Maybe.
I'm not too sure, though.

24:33.515 --> 24:35.822
- Mi'jita,what are
you not telling me?

24:35.865 --> 24:38.999
♪

24:39.042 --> 24:41.349
Is your--is your mama dating
someone already?

24:41.392 --> 24:42.698
- I don't know.
I have no idea.

24:42.742 --> 24:44.134
If you want to talk to Mom

24:44.178 --> 24:46.702
about her personal life,
then do it.

24:46.746 --> 24:48.530
In case you haven't noticed,
I'm trying to deal

24:48.574 --> 24:49.879
with my own kind of breakup.

24:51.577 --> 24:54.144
- Oh, I'm--I'm so sorry.

24:54.188 --> 24:55.624
You're right.

24:55.668 --> 24:57.931
- Dad, I didn't--
I didn't mean it like that .

24:57.974 --> 24:59.323
- No.
- It's just that, you know--

24:59.367 --> 25:02.544
- I got to go
get Soph anyway.

25:02.588 --> 25:04.764
You just keep writing
your music, okay?

25:04.807 --> 25:07.854
It's really good.
- Thank you.

25:07.897 --> 25:11.771
♪

25:11.814 --> 25:13.947
[door opens, closes]

25:13.990 --> 25:16.558
[exhales deeply, strums chord]

25:16.602 --> 25:19.256
[line trilling]

25:19.300 --> 25:21.258
- Hey, you've reached Tonya.
Leave a message.

25:21.302 --> 25:22.651
[line beeps]
- Hey, Tonya.

25:22.695 --> 25:26.394
It's, uh--it's Kyle.

25:26.437 --> 25:28.918
Listen, can you give me
a call when you get a chance?

25:28.962 --> 25:32.792
[distant telephone ringing]

25:32.835 --> 25:34.837
- Mayor Lang, Lois Lane
is here to see you.

25:37.448 --> 25:39.494
- Thanks, Beau.

25:42.715 --> 25:43.890
The office looks great.

25:43.933 --> 25:45.500
- Lois, I'm really busy
right now.

25:45.544 --> 25:47.241
- I know, so I will cut
to the chase.

25:47.284 --> 25:49.591
I came here to tell you
what I should have told you

25:49.635 --> 25:52.420
this morning,
which is that I am sorry.

25:52.463 --> 25:53.943
Sometimes I forget

25:53.987 --> 25:56.163
how important
those two little words are.

25:56.206 --> 25:58.948
You were right.
I was really selfish.

25:58.992 --> 26:00.646
I wanted to be your friend,
and I didn't think

26:00.689 --> 26:02.386
about whether
it was fair to you.

26:04.258 --> 26:05.825
You have
to understand, Lana,

26:05.868 --> 26:08.567
my life was so different
in Metropolis.

26:08.610 --> 26:09.872
The boys were little.

26:09.916 --> 26:11.439
I was working
around the clock.

26:11.482 --> 26:13.484
I didn't have time
for friends.

26:13.528 --> 26:16.096
So it was easy
to keep the secret.

26:16.139 --> 26:18.489
And then we moved here, and
you and I started hanging out,

26:18.533 --> 26:19.969
and I felt this connection.

26:20.013 --> 26:22.276
- Yeah.
I felt it, too.

26:22.319 --> 26:24.452
- I hadn't had
a real girlfriend

26:24.495 --> 26:27.063
since my sister
and I had our falling-out.

26:27.107 --> 26:28.761
I didn't want to give it up.

26:28.804 --> 26:32.068
So I convinced myself
that it was Clark's secret.

26:32.112 --> 26:33.635
And that wasn't true.

26:33.679 --> 26:35.506
Listen, I know
it's gonna take a lot of time

26:35.550 --> 26:38.727
to earn back your trust,
but I want to start now.

26:38.771 --> 26:40.816
- [scoffs]
What do you mean by now?

26:40.860 --> 26:43.297
- Clark being Superman
is just the tip of the iceberg.

26:43.340 --> 26:45.125
There's a lot more
you need to know.

26:45.168 --> 26:46.605
Once you have
all that information,

26:46.648 --> 26:48.041
you can decide
what to do with it.

26:48.084 --> 26:50.609
- I didn't even realize
I had a choice.

26:50.652 --> 26:52.480
- Of course you do.

26:52.523 --> 26:54.700
We love you, Lana.

26:56.702 --> 26:59.618
It's up to you whether or not
you decide to tell your family.

27:02.533 --> 27:04.579
Let's start with Jordan.

27:06.712 --> 27:10.237
Turns out he takes
after his dad.

27:10.280 --> 27:12.282
- Oh.

27:12.326 --> 27:19.202
♪

27:19.246 --> 27:21.596
- Interesting location.

27:21.640 --> 27:23.076
Couldn't have found

27:23.119 --> 27:25.513
an abandoned
tropical beach somewhere?

27:25.556 --> 27:28.951
♪

27:28.995 --> 27:31.650
- I think we'd all feel better
if what's left of the pendant

27:31.693 --> 27:34.609
when you're done winds up
at the bottom of that volcano.

27:34.653 --> 27:37.612
- Very well, then.
Shall we?

27:42.051 --> 27:44.010
- Whenever you're ready.

27:49.755 --> 27:51.582
- It's working.

27:57.240 --> 27:59.242
Wait.
What the hell just happened?

27:59.286 --> 28:04.900
♪

28:04.944 --> 28:08.208
- I'm taking back
what's mine.

28:16.216 --> 28:18.871
- So that's what
becoming whole looks like.

28:18.914 --> 28:21.308
We can't have that,
now, can we?

28:23.484 --> 28:25.094
- Tal!

28:27.270 --> 28:29.403
- [groaning]

28:29.446 --> 28:32.406
[dramatic music]

28:32.449 --> 28:39.456
♪

28:41.894 --> 28:43.983
- Tal.

28:44.026 --> 28:45.549
- What did she just do to me?

28:45.593 --> 28:51.468
♪

28:53.035 --> 28:53.993
- Superman!

28:54.036 --> 28:55.168
- Tal's down.

28:55.211 --> 28:57.039
Ally's got the pendant.

28:57.083 --> 28:59.128
We have to stop her
before she gets to the portal.

28:59.172 --> 29:00.956
- On my way.
Fire up the suit!

29:01.000 --> 29:02.131
[device whirring]

29:02.175 --> 29:09.225
♪

29:23.283 --> 29:25.807
- John, she's got Superman.
You need to hurry.

29:25.851 --> 29:31.726
♪

29:31.770 --> 29:33.336
- Lock on target.

29:33.380 --> 29:36.862
- I told you, Superman,
we would become gods.

29:36.905 --> 29:43.825
♪

29:43.869 --> 29:44.957
- Aah!

29:50.136 --> 29:57.186
♪

30:02.844 --> 30:04.715
- I don't have
much left, brother.

30:04.759 --> 30:06.239
- Neither do I.

30:07.849 --> 30:09.111
- Make it quick.

30:09.155 --> 30:16.205
♪

30:23.386 --> 30:25.475
- Together, then.

30:25.519 --> 30:32.569
♪

30:40.795 --> 30:42.101
- Almost there.

30:43.450 --> 30:44.799
Give it everything you got!

30:44.843 --> 30:48.455
[both screaming]

30:54.287 --> 30:56.289
- No!

30:56.332 --> 30:59.031
[screaming continues]

30:59.074 --> 31:05.167
♪

31:06.299 --> 31:08.040
- [exhales sharply in relief]

31:08.083 --> 31:15.134
♪

31:22.793 --> 31:24.795
- [breathes deeply]

31:24.839 --> 31:31.890
♪

31:36.111 --> 31:38.635
[breathing heavily]

31:38.679 --> 31:39.767
- Tal?

31:39.810 --> 31:46.861
♪

31:49.385 --> 31:51.431
- We should've kept him
in cuffs.

31:58.786 --> 32:00.353
- What do you mean
she stole your power?

32:00.396 --> 32:02.007
- Not stole exactly...

32:02.050 --> 32:04.574
more like siphoned.

32:04.618 --> 32:07.403
She was feeding off my energy
to make herself stronger.

32:07.447 --> 32:09.144
I felt
that sensation before.

32:09.188 --> 32:10.667
- When?

32:10.711 --> 32:12.887
- When I tried
to stop her from merging.

32:12.931 --> 32:15.803
Today was ten times worse.

32:15.846 --> 32:17.109
But at least now,
with the pendant destroyed,

32:17.152 --> 32:18.762
it won't happen
to anyone else,

32:18.806 --> 32:20.634
which means we only have
to worry about Ally.

32:20.677 --> 32:22.244
- And Tal-Rho.

32:22.288 --> 32:24.246
- I wouldn't worry
about him.

32:24.290 --> 32:25.987
- What? So dude brings you
some flowers,

32:26.031 --> 32:27.336
and then all is forgiven?

32:27.380 --> 32:29.599
- He risked his life
to save ours,

32:29.643 --> 32:31.340
not once but twice.

32:31.384 --> 32:33.342
And they weren't just flowers.
They were peonies.

32:33.386 --> 32:35.910
- Destroying the pendant
didn't solve our problem.

32:35.954 --> 32:40.045
It only enraged Ally,
which means she'll be back.

32:40.088 --> 32:43.309
So now we have an enemy
who can steal Superman's powers

32:43.352 --> 32:47.008
and potentially use them
against us.

32:47.052 --> 32:49.402
How the hell do we defeat
something like that?

32:49.445 --> 32:52.405
[dramatic music]

32:52.448 --> 32:55.886
♪

32:59.499 --> 33:02.415
- Are you making dinner?
- It's just salad and hot dogs.

33:02.458 --> 33:04.460
But the salad does have
pumpkin seeds,

33:04.504 --> 33:06.419
so you can tell
an effort has been made.

33:06.462 --> 33:10.597
- I mean,
you are literally the best.

33:10.640 --> 33:12.425
Thank you.
- [chuckles]

33:12.468 --> 33:14.079
Yeah.
I'm just trying to help.

33:14.122 --> 33:17.212
I can tell you've been
overwhelmed lately, so...

33:17.256 --> 33:18.866
Uh...

33:18.909 --> 33:23.218
so Dad picking us up
from school...

33:23.262 --> 33:24.872
you must be really busy.

33:24.915 --> 33:26.787
- Was everything okay
with your dad?

33:26.830 --> 33:28.615
- Yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah.

33:28.658 --> 33:31.357
It's just I think that you guys
need to have a conversation.

33:31.400 --> 33:32.793
- What about?

33:32.836 --> 33:34.447
- Come on, Mom,
Dad's not an idiot.

33:34.490 --> 33:36.318
He can tell
when something's up with you.

33:36.362 --> 33:38.886
It's just...

33:38.929 --> 33:41.932
if you are dating
somebody, then--

33:41.976 --> 33:45.284
- Dating someone?
Why on Earth would I even--

33:45.327 --> 33:47.242
- I don't want to hear
about it.

33:47.286 --> 33:49.244
In fact, I'd, like, rather you
never speak to me about that.

33:49.288 --> 33:51.464
I'm just saying
that if you--

33:51.507 --> 33:54.075
if you are totally over Dad,
then you should tell him,

33:54.119 --> 33:55.685
'cause he does deserveto know.

33:55.729 --> 33:57.731
- Honey,
I'm not dating anyone.

33:57.774 --> 34:00.908
- So then what is it?

34:00.951 --> 34:03.998
'Cause you have been acting
kind of weird.

34:04.042 --> 34:07.262
♪

34:07.306 --> 34:11.049
Whatever it is,
you--you can trust me with it.

34:11.092 --> 34:12.267
- I know I can.

34:12.311 --> 34:14.704
♪

34:14.748 --> 34:16.271
I know.

34:16.315 --> 34:17.751
Come here.

34:17.794 --> 34:19.970
- Is everything okay?

34:20.014 --> 34:23.713
- Everything is fine...
okay?

34:23.757 --> 34:26.238
I just, uh...

34:26.281 --> 34:28.544
I just learned something
that's kind of a big deal,

34:28.588 --> 34:30.503
and I want to share it
with you.

34:32.505 --> 34:33.810
- Sarah.

34:33.854 --> 34:36.030
SSSniperWolf just posted
a new video.

34:36.074 --> 34:37.727
Come watch with me.
- Okay, I'll--

34:37.771 --> 34:40.295
I'll be there in a second.

34:42.297 --> 34:44.517
God, she's growing upso fast.

34:44.560 --> 34:46.519
♪

34:46.562 --> 34:50.131
Um, I'm sorry, Mom.
What were you saying?

34:50.175 --> 34:52.002
- Oh, uh, yeah.

34:52.046 --> 34:55.658
Uh, uh, there's an internship

34:55.702 --> 34:57.704
available in my office,

34:57.747 --> 35:00.359
and I know that you're looking
to beef up your college résumé,

35:00.402 --> 35:02.143
so I figure...

35:02.187 --> 35:04.798
- Internship, uh...

35:04.841 --> 35:07.366
Y-yeah.
Do you mind if I--

35:07.409 --> 35:08.584
if I think about it?

35:08.628 --> 35:11.109
- Oh, absolutely.
Take your time.

35:11.152 --> 35:12.893
[knock at door]

35:12.936 --> 35:15.287
- Uh, I'll grab it.
- Oh, it's okay. I'll get it.

35:15.330 --> 35:17.593
You go be with your sister.

35:17.637 --> 35:21.162
♪

35:21.206 --> 35:22.511
- Hey.

35:22.555 --> 35:26.167
Can we talk somewhere...

35:26.211 --> 35:28.387
in private?

35:28.430 --> 35:30.215
[laughter]

35:30.258 --> 35:31.999
- Okay, okay, when that boulder

35:32.042 --> 35:33.870
was going to fall
on your head,

35:33.914 --> 35:35.568
all right, I swear,
I almost let it hit you.

35:35.611 --> 35:37.047
- No, but we were so close.

35:37.091 --> 35:38.658
- Okay, but we can
always go back tomorrow.

35:38.701 --> 35:40.268
- Okay, we got to get
to school eventually,

35:40.312 --> 35:41.791
'cause I have a sandwich
in my locker,

35:41.835 --> 35:46.144
and it will start to smell.
[laughter]

35:46.187 --> 35:47.667
- What's happening here?

35:47.710 --> 35:49.669
- You know,
just a little family bonding.

35:49.712 --> 35:51.279
- Okay.

35:51.323 --> 35:53.107
I like seeing that.

35:53.151 --> 35:55.849
So how was school?
Anything exciting happen?

35:55.892 --> 35:57.764
both: No.
- Very dull.

35:59.548 --> 36:01.071
- Okay.

36:01.115 --> 36:04.466
Well, your dad and I had
a very productive day.

36:04.510 --> 36:06.425
- What happened?
- Did you seal the portal?

36:06.468 --> 36:09.515
- We may not need to anymore.
The pendant has been destroyed.

36:09.558 --> 36:10.907
- No way!
You're kidding!

36:10.951 --> 36:13.171
So what--I mean,
Ally can't force

36:13.214 --> 36:14.476
anyone else
to merge, then, right?

36:14.520 --> 36:16.217
- Yeah, that--
that may be so, but, like,

36:16.261 --> 36:17.827
she's still out there
somewhere.

36:17.871 --> 36:19.655
- Yeah.

36:19.699 --> 36:21.831
You boys want to stay
for dinner?

36:21.875 --> 36:23.398
- Sure.
- Cool.

36:23.442 --> 36:26.053
Text your folks,
then you can help us make it.

36:26.096 --> 36:28.621
- Saw that coming.

36:28.664 --> 36:30.449
- You got it?
- Yeah.

36:30.492 --> 36:33.016
- Come on,
I'm not making it by myself.

36:35.497 --> 36:39.719
[keypad clicking]

36:41.938 --> 36:44.637
[phone buzzes]

36:44.680 --> 36:51.644
♪

36:52.949 --> 36:53.994
- Oh.

36:54.037 --> 36:55.996
Hi, Mr. and Mrs. Kent.

36:56.039 --> 36:57.693
- Hey, Sarah.

36:57.737 --> 36:59.869
- Mom, do you mind if I go out
with Dad for a bit?

36:59.913 --> 37:02.524
- Sure.
Just be back by 10:00.

37:02.568 --> 37:05.745
- Okay.
Uh, bye, guys.

37:07.703 --> 37:09.096
- [whispering]
Did you tell her?

37:09.139 --> 37:10.880
- I couldn't.

37:10.924 --> 37:13.274
Not because she wouldn't
be able to handle it,

37:13.318 --> 37:16.321
but I can't ask her to lie
to her sister or her father,

37:16.364 --> 37:18.279
for that matter.

37:18.323 --> 37:19.846
It's not fair to Sarah.

37:19.889 --> 37:21.456
- That makes sense.

37:21.500 --> 37:25.286
- So I have a doppelganger

37:25.330 --> 37:28.115
somewhere out there who may try
to come and kill me.

37:28.158 --> 37:29.899
- I'm not gonna let
that happen.

37:29.943 --> 37:33.120
We're just making you aware
as the situation unfolds,

37:33.163 --> 37:35.296
not because there's anything
you should do right now.

37:35.340 --> 37:37.255
- Is Smallville in danger?

37:37.298 --> 37:38.908
- Honestly,
we can't be sure of anything

37:38.952 --> 37:40.388
as long as Ally's
still out there.

37:40.432 --> 37:42.172
We just wanted you to know
what we know.

37:42.216 --> 37:44.479
Like you said in your
interview, full transparency.

37:44.523 --> 37:45.915
- I appreciate that.

37:45.959 --> 37:48.135
And I want you both to know
that even though

37:48.178 --> 37:52.444
it's gonna take some time
to get over the...hurt,

37:52.487 --> 37:54.489
I will get over it.

37:54.533 --> 37:56.448
And I'm not mad
at either of you.

37:56.491 --> 38:00.147
- [chuckles softly]
I'm really happy to hear that.

38:00.190 --> 38:03.281
- But I also can't have you
in my life right now--

38:03.324 --> 38:05.195
not just mine, but my kids'.

38:05.239 --> 38:07.502
I don't want to feel like
I'm lying to them

38:07.546 --> 38:09.809
every time
our families are together.

38:09.852 --> 38:11.680
And I think it would be easier
for everyone

38:11.724 --> 38:13.682
if we just made a clean break.

38:13.726 --> 38:16.381
♪

38:16.424 --> 38:18.165
- Lana, please.

38:18.208 --> 38:21.429
- I'm sorry, but that's just
the way it has to be right now.

38:21.473 --> 38:23.562
♪

38:23.605 --> 38:28.175
[indistinct chatter]

38:28.218 --> 38:30.308
- Um, I know
I'm pretty mature for my age,

38:30.351 --> 38:32.658
but you know I'm not
actually 21, right?

38:32.701 --> 38:34.355
- Yeah, I'm aware.

38:34.399 --> 38:36.705
- Okay.

38:36.749 --> 38:38.968
Wait, is this...

38:39.012 --> 38:41.231
No, no, no, I'm not here
to meet your old hookup.

38:41.275 --> 38:43.103
- No. No. No, no, no.
You're not.

38:43.146 --> 38:46.498
Okay, look, she doesn't
even work here anymore.

38:46.541 --> 38:50.023
But she, uh--
she did do us a solid.

38:50.066 --> 38:52.504
It's open-mic night,

38:52.547 --> 38:55.376
you know, and I heard that--
what was it, Billie Eilish?--

38:55.420 --> 38:57.160
well, she got famous
when she was 11.

38:57.204 --> 39:00.076
So I figured, uh, why not
launch the next big thing

39:00.120 --> 39:01.426
right here in Smallville?

39:01.469 --> 39:03.471
- Dad, I'm not
the next big thing.

39:03.515 --> 39:06.779
- Oh, but that's
the goal, right?

39:06.822 --> 39:08.650
Come on,
you got to start somewhere.

39:08.694 --> 39:10.696
Tonya cleared everything
with the manager.

39:10.739 --> 39:12.785
Hey, look,
she feels as badly

39:12.828 --> 39:15.744
about what happenedas I do.

39:15.788 --> 39:17.398
- Yeah, I'm sure she does.

39:17.442 --> 39:19.705
- Okay, stage is open.

39:19.748 --> 39:20.967
- Why don't you just
get up there

39:21.010 --> 39:22.316
and show 'em
what you got, hmm?

39:22.360 --> 39:23.926
- Right now?
- Yeah.

39:23.970 --> 39:25.014
- No.

39:27.626 --> 39:30.411
Um...
- Andale.

39:30.455 --> 39:31.891
You got this.

39:34.850 --> 39:36.417
- Hey, y'all.

39:36.461 --> 39:41.117
Uh, I'm Sarah Cortez,
and these are my songs.

39:44.338 --> 39:47.297
[light guitar music playing]

39:47.341 --> 39:54.000
♪

39:55.741 --> 40:00.615
♪ They say love is the way,
but that can't be right ♪

40:00.659 --> 40:03.836
♪ When every happy ever after

40:03.879 --> 40:06.621
♪ Ends in goodbye

40:06.665 --> 40:09.537
♪ There's a voice telling me
this anxiety will cease ♪

40:09.581 --> 40:12.279
♪ And I'll know it all

40:12.322 --> 40:15.151
♪ I'm reaching for the stars
and hoping ♪

40:15.195 --> 40:18.111
♪ That the sky won't fall

40:18.154 --> 40:21.680
♪ I'm tired of it all

40:21.723 --> 40:23.682
- Then it's over.

40:23.725 --> 40:24.683
We've lost.

40:24.726 --> 40:26.075
- We haven't lost.

40:26.119 --> 40:27.947
- But without the pendant?

40:27.990 --> 40:30.428
- There are other ways.

40:30.471 --> 40:32.430
[door closes]

40:32.473 --> 40:36.608
♪

40:36.651 --> 40:39.393
- Where's Lana?
I want to talk to Lana.

40:39.437 --> 40:41.874
- That's not gonna happen...

40:41.917 --> 40:44.311
ever again.

40:44.354 --> 40:46.705
- I saw what happened
when you merged.

40:46.748 --> 40:48.358
I saw your fear.

40:50.056 --> 40:52.624
Your plan to save everyone,

40:52.667 --> 40:54.669
it's not gonna work.

40:54.713 --> 40:56.671
I should have listened
to my brother.

40:56.715 --> 40:58.891
You are no savior.

40:58.934 --> 41:00.719
- [echoing]
Not yet.

41:02.155 --> 41:04.374
- [groaning]

41:04.418 --> 41:07.682
[screaming]

41:07.726 --> 41:14.689
♪

41:14.733 --> 41:17.779
- [gasps]

41:17.823 --> 41:21.435
♪

41:21.479 --> 41:23.785
[echoing]
But I will be.

41:23.829 --> 41:29.922
♪

41:52.335 --> 41:55.382
- Greg, move your head.
